Schema change (additive):
  ✓ composio_poll_state gained `workspace_id UUID NOT NULL` (table
    was empty in prod; backfill via JOIN against automations is a
    no-op).
  ✓ FK constraint
    `composio_poll_state_workspace_id_workspaces_id_fk` REFERENCES
    workspaces(id) ON DELETE CASCADE — additive to the existing
    automation_id FK CASCADE.
  ✓ Partial index
    `composio_poll_state_workspace_due_idx (workspace_id,
    next_poll_at) WHERE paused_at IS NULL` — matches the H.3 CTE's
    window PARTITION BY workspace_id ORDER BY next_poll_at and the
    outer WHERE next_poll_at <= now() AND paused_at IS NULL.

Sweep query (H.1 + H.2 + H.3 combined):
  ```sql
  WITH ranked AS (
    SELECT id,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY workspace_id ORDER BY next_poll_at) AS rn
      FROM public.composio_poll_state
     WHERE next_poll_at <= now() AND paused_at IS NULL
  )
  SELECT cps.id, cps.automation_id::text AS automation_id,
         cps.trigger_index, cps.toolkit, cps.event, cps.filters,
         cps.state, cps.composio_user_id, cps.connected_account_id,
         cps.consecutive_failures
    FROM public.composio_poll_state cps
    JOIN ranked r ON r.id = cps.id
   WHERE r.rn <= $POLL_PER_WORKSPACE_CAP
   ORDER BY cps.next_poll_at ASC
   LIMIT $POLL_BATCH_SIZE
     FOR UPDATE OF cps SKIP LOCKED
  ```

Behavior contract (per H.3 spec):
  ✓ ROW_NUMBER OVER (PARTITION BY workspace_id ORDER BY
    next_poll_at) ranks due rows within each workspace.
  ✓ rn <= POLL_PER_WORKSPACE_CAP caps each workspace at 5
    rows/sweep (default).
  ✓ Outer ORDER BY next_poll_at + LIMIT POLL_BATCH_SIZE keeps the
    global "process oldest first" intent.
  ✓ FOR UPDATE OF cps SKIP LOCKED locks the composio_poll_state
    base rows (not the CTE virtual rows), so the H.1 atomic-claim
    + tentative-lease semantics still hold.
  ✓ Boundary cases:
      - 100 workspaces × 1 row each → all 100 in rn=1 set; LIMIT
        50 picks 50 oldest. Each workspace gets at most 1 row.
      - 10 workspaces × 10 rows each → rn<=5 set is 50 rows
        (5 each); LIMIT 50 picks all. Even distribution.
      - 1 workspace × 100 rows → rn<=5 set is 5; LIMIT 50 picks 5.
        Other workspaces get the remaining 45 slots. (No starvation.)

